Two tankers have exploded at the popular Otedola Bridge in Lagos. The Lagos State Emergency Management Agency, after responding to distress calls from the area, said a 40fit containerized truck loaded with fabric had a brake failure while moving inward Berger. It said the truck then collided with a tanker loaded with 33000 liters of PMS, which resulted in a fire outbreak. The explosion reportedly occurred around 2am. The casualty figure was unknown as at the time of filing this report.